# Handover Document: Monitoring Dashboard

## 1. Project Overview
A production-grade Server Monitoring Dashboard using **React 18, TypeScript, React Router v7, Tailwind CSS, Recharts, and Lucide React**. It visualizes real-time metrics (CPU, Memory, Alerts, Network, Databases, etc.) sourced from a **Spring Boot** backend that aggregates data from **Prometheus**.

## 2. What Has Been Completed
- **Frontend Infrastructure setup:** Vite + React + TS, with Tailwind CSS styling and dark theme configuration. Base layouts (sidebar, header, routing) are fully implemented.
- **Component System:** Reusable UI components like [Badge](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/components/ui/badge.tsx#9-24), [Switch](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/components/ui/switch.tsx#9-26), progress bars, [MetricCard](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/components/metric-card.tsx#12-43), [ServersTable](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/components/servers-table.tsx#34-115), [AlertsPanel](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/components/alerts-panel.tsx#6-81), and [DatabasePanel](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/components/database-panel.tsx#30-121).
- **API Service Layer ([src/services/api.ts](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/services/api.ts)):** Centralized `fetch` wrapper connecting to the Spring Boot backend (`http://localhost:8080`). Includes a custom [useFetch](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/hooks/useFetch.ts#10-43) hook with auto-polling capabilities.
- **Wired Pages & Data Integration:**
  - **Dashboard (`/`):** Hooked up to `/api/dashboard/stats` for metric cards, `/api/dashboard/history` for historical charts, and `/api/dashboard/databases` for real Database Monitoring panels.
  - **Servers (`/servers`):** Wired to `/api/dashboard/summary` for a list of servers with live CPU/RAM/Disk/Network/Status. Also fetches average CPU trend for the last 24h via `/history`.
  - **Alerts (`/alerts`):** Wired to `/api/dashboard/alerts`. Merges backend live alerts with some placeholder app-level static alerts for UX. Supports filtering and acknowledging (state kept in UI).
  - **Databases (`/databases`):** Wired to `/api/dashboard/databases`. Calculates dynamic DB metrics for Active Databases, Connections, and TPS across the infrastructure, and plots a generic query latency area chart per DB.
- **TypeScript Fixes:** Resolved Vite/esbuild `isolatedModules` errors by enforcing `import type { ... }` for TypeScript interfaces.

## 3. Current State & Architecture
- **Backend Port:** Fixed to `http://localhost:8080`.
- **Frontend Port:** Runs on `localhost:5173` via `npm run dev`.
- **Mocked Pages (Pending API integration):**
  - **Applications (`/applications`):** Currently uses static mock data. Needs a backend endpoint (`/api/dashboard/applications`) for application-level metrics (e.g., uptime, RPS, error rates per app).
  - **Logs (`/logs`):** Currently uses static mock data. Needs a backend endpoint (`/api/dashboard/logs`) to fetch system/app logs, filterable by severity string.
  - **Settings (`/settings`):** Fully built UI, but state is not persisted to backend yet.

## 4. Next Steps for the Next AI
1. **Verify Complete Functionality:** Ensure `npm run dev` yields no console errors indicating missing exports, by fully navigating between the Dashboard, Servers, Alerts, and Databases pages.
2. **Implement Remaining Backend Endpoints:**
   - Create endpoints in the Spring Boot backend to serve data for Applications (`/api/dashboard/applications`), and Logs (`/api/dashboard/logs`).
3. **Wire Remaining Frontend Pages:**
   - Update [src/app/pages/applications.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/pages/applications.tsx), and [logs.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/app/pages/logs.tsx) to use the [useFetch](file:///c:/Users/Ouma/Desktop/monitoring%20dashboard/monitoring-frontend/src/hooks/useFetch.ts#10-43) hook and call the newly created backend endpoints.
4. **Backend Database Persistence (Optional):**
   - The settings page currently has non-persisted state. Integrating a settings endpoint (`PUT /api/settings`) to persist user preferences.
5. **Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS):**
   - Make sure `CorsConfig` in the Spring Boot app continues to allow `http://localhost:5173`. Any fetch failures are likely CORS if the backend is running.
